findings.description:
The schema pattern `^[^
]*\S[^
]*$` forbids 
 but does NOT forbid , 	, NUL, or RS (0x1e). With `mapfile -t` reading newline-separated jq output, a value containing  will not split lines but WILL appear as the trailing byte of a field — not a shift, but downstream string comparisons (`*"$expected_absent_marker"*` glob match) will fail to find a marker that the author thought they specified. More importantly, a value containing NUL byte (0x00) inside JSON is invalid JSON anyway — but values with embedded RS (which IS the actual concern of RT-TC-101) ARE allowed by the pattern. The author claims the pattern 'forbids the mapfile-shift bypass class' but mapfile splits ONLY on 
 by default, so the pattern is correct for that — however the description of 'bypass class' is overstated.
